The paper deals with privacy mechanisms and their statistical properties, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) communities. The use of differential privacy and its variants also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the focus on statistical analysis and bounds on privacy guarantees may also be relevant to the statistics (cs.SI) community.
